        <updateDate>2021-12-03T22:13:05Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Stopping Illicit Trafficking Act of 2021 or the SIFT Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill adds five fentanyl analogues and the entire category of fentanyl-related substances to schedule I of the Controlled Substances Act. A schedule I controlled substance is a drug, substance, or chemical that has a high potential for abuse; has no currently accepted medical value; and is subject to regulatory controls and administrative, civil, and criminal penalties under the Controlled Substances Act.</p> <p>The bill also creates a process to remove from schedule I certain fentanyl-related substances that do not have a high potential for abuse.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
